Problem: Vaccine Dates
Topic: Implementation
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Compare the given day with the allowed range 
[
𝑙
,
𝑟
]
[l,r]. If the day is before the range, it is too early; if after, it is too late; otherwise, it is the correct time to take the dose.

Time Complexity: O(1)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
	// your code goes here
    int t=0;
    cin>>t;
    while(t--){
        int d,l,r;
        cin>>d>>l>>r;
        if(d>r)
            cout<<"Too Late"<<endl;
        
        else if(d<l)
            cout<<"Too Early"<<endl;
        
        else
            cout<<"Take second dose now"<<endl;
        
    }
    return 0;
}

